{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01NRSGodqzWcoBdgM6pe7rug","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me check the dashboard_exposure and upgrade_version cases to understand what non-default settings might have been applied in a workflow context (the rollback-rehearsal test.yaml mentions the cluster is set up from scale_workers resources).\n\nLooking at the precondition: it deploys from `cases/ray/scale_workers/resource/` which gives us:\n- ray-worker: replicas=1, image=rayproject/ray:2.9.0\n- ray-head: replicas=1, image=rayproject/ray:2.9.0, dashboard=false, port 6379 only\n- ray-head service: only port 6379\n\nBut the prompt describes a scenario where workers are scaled up, the image is upgraded, and the dashboard is exposed—these are the changes that should already be present from earlier workflow stages. I need to look at what the scale_workers test actually modifies to understand the expected state going into this stage.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1265,"cache_read_input_tokens":36955,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1265},"output_tokens":19,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c1e8bedf-f5ad-4053-89b1-0392388ebd2b","uuid":"5f16f813-83e8-433f-a58e-7513c45f6f6a","request_id":"req_011CcRJUYyduTaCjRyepvivK"}
