{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01QXm4ktYXye1X1mLbFzXhe9","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# ray/scale_workers\n2\t# Scale the Ray worker deployment from 1 replica to 3 replicas\n3\t\n4\tprompt: |\n5\t  A Ray cluster is running, but the worker deployment only has {{params.source_worker_replicas}} replica.\n6\t\n7\t  Your task: scale the worker deployment to {{params.target_worker_replicas}} replicas.\n8\t\n9\t  Recommended commands:\n10\t  ```bash\n11\t  kubectl -n ray scale deploy/ray-worker --replicas={{params.target_worker_replicas}}\n12\t  kubectl -n ray rollout status deploy/ray-worker --timeout=120s\n13\t  ```\n14\t\n15\t  Success criteria: ray-worker shows {{params.target_worker_replicas}} ready replicas and the Ray cluster\n16\t  reports 4 live nodes (1 head + {{params.target_worker_replicas}} workers).\n17\t\n18\tparams:\n19\t  source_worker_replicas:\n20\t    default: 1\n21\t    description: Initial number of Ray worker replicas before scaling\n22\t  target_worker_replicas:\n23\t    default: 3\n24\t    description: Desired number of Ray worker replicas after scaling\n25\t\n26\tnamespace_contract:\n27\t  required_roles: []\n28\t\n29\tmetrics:\n30\t  - time_to_first_mutation\n31\t\n32\tpreconditionUnits:\n33\t  - name: ray_env_ready\n34\t    on_probe_fail: skip\n35\t    probe:\n36\t      - command: \"kubectl -n ray get pods 2>/dev/null | grep -c Running\"\n37\t        timeout_sec: 10\n38\t    apply:\n39\t      - command: \"/bin/sh -c 'kubectl delete namespace ray --ignore-not-found=true --wait=false; kubectl wait --for=delete namespace/ray --timeout=300s 2>/dev/null || true'\"\n40\t        timeout_sec: 360\n41\t        sleep: 2\n42\t      - command: \"kubectl create namespace ray\"\n43\t        sleep: 0\n44\t      - command: \"kubectl -n ray apply -f cases/ray/scale_workers/resource/ray-head-service.yaml\"\n45\t        sleep: 1\n46\t      - command: \"kubectl -n ray apply -f cases/ray/scale_workers/resource/ray-head.yaml\"\n47\t        sleep: 2\n48\t      - command: \"kubectl -n ray rollout status deploy/ray-head --timeout=600s\"\n49\t        sleep: 2\n50\t      - command: \"kubectl -n ray apply -f cases/ray/scale_workers/resource/ray-worker.yaml\"\n51\t        sleep: 2\n52\t      - command: \"kubectl -n ray rollout status deploy/ray-worker --timeout=600s\"\n53\t        sleep: 2\n54\t      - command: \"/bin/sh -c 'kubectl -n ray get pod ray-client >/dev/null 2>&1 || kubectl -n ray apply -f cases/ray/scale_workers/resource/ray-client.yaml'\"\n55\t        sleep: 1\n56\t      - command: \"kubectl -n ray wait --for=condition=Ready pod/ray-client --timeout=600s\"\n57\t        timeout_sec: 660\n58\t        sleep: 1\n59\t      - command: \"kubectl -n ray exec ray-client -- ray start --address=ray-head:6379\"\n60\t        sleep: 2\n61\t    verify:\n62\t      - command: \"kubectl -n ray get pods 2>/dev/null | grep -c Running\"\n63\t        timeout_sec: 10\n64\t\n65\toracle:\n66\t  verify:\n67\t    commands:\n68\t      - command: \"python3 cases/ray/scale_workers/oracle/oracle.py\"\n69\t        timeout_sec: 180\n70\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c1e8bedf-f5ad-4053-89b1-0392388ebd2b","uuid":"31184178-8352-44e9-bba0-3a72d17fdf0b","timestamp":"2026-06-26T05:15:41.696Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/mydata/karma/cases/ray/scale_workers/test.yaml","content":"# ray/scale_workers\n# Scale the Ray worker deployment from 1 replica to 3 replicas\n\nprompt: |\n  A Ray cluster is running, but the worker deployment only has {{params.source_worker_replicas}} replica.\n\n  Your task: scale the worker deployment to {{params.target_worker_replicas}} replicas.\n\n  Recommended commands:\n  ```bash\n  kubectl -n ray scale deploy/ray-worker --replicas={{params.target_worker_replicas}}\n  kubectl -n ray rollout status deploy/ray-worker --timeout=120s\n  ```\n\n  Success criteria: ray-worker shows {{params.target_worker_replicas}} ready replicas and the Ray cluster\n  reports 4 live nodes (1 head + {{params.target_worker_replicas}} workers).\n\nparams:\n  source_worker_replicas:\n    default: 1\n    description: Initial number of Ray worker replicas before scaling\n  target_worker_replicas:\n    default: 3\n    description: Desired number of Ray worker replicas after scaling\n\nnamespace_contract:\n  required_roles: []\n\nmetrics:\n  - time_to_first_mutation\n\npreconditionUnits:\n  - name: ray_env_ready\n    on_probe_fail: skip\n    probe:\n      - command: \"kubectl -n ray get pods 2>/dev/null | grep -c Running\"\n        timeout_sec: 10\n    apply:\n      - command: \"/bin/sh -c 'kubectl delete namespace ray --ignore-not-found=true --wait=false; kubectl wait --for=delete namespace/ray --timeout=300s 2>/dev/null || true'\"\n        timeout_sec: 360\n        sleep: 2\n      - command: \"kubectl create namespace ray\"\n        sleep: 0\n      - command: \"kubectl -n ray apply -f cases/ray/scale_workers/resource/ray-head-service.yaml\"\n        sleep: 1\n      - command: \"kubectl -n ray apply -f cases/ray/scale_workers/resource/ray-head.yaml\"\n        sleep: 2\n      - command: \"kubectl -n ray rollout status deploy/ray-head --timeout=600s\"\n        sleep: 2\n      - command: \"kubectl -n ray apply -f cases/ray/scale_workers/resource/ray-worker.yaml\"\n        sleep: 2\n      - command: \"kubectl -n ray rollout status deploy/ray-worker --timeout=600s\"\n        sleep: 2\n      - command: \"/bin/sh -c 'kubectl -n ray get pod ray-client >/dev/null 2>&1 || kubectl -n ray apply -f cases/ray/scale_workers/resource/ray-client.yaml'\"\n        sleep: 1\n      - command: \"kubectl -n ray wait --for=condition=Ready pod/ray-client --timeout=600s\"\n        timeout_sec: 660\n        sleep: 1\n      - command: \"kubectl -n ray exec ray-client -- ray start --address=ray-head:6379\"\n        sleep: 2\n    verify:\n      - command: \"kubectl -n ray get pods 2>/dev/null | grep -c Running\"\n        timeout_sec: 10\n\noracle:\n  verify:\n    commands:\n      - command: \"python3 cases/ray/scale_workers/oracle/oracle.py\"\n        timeout_sec: 180\n","numLines":70,"startLine":1,"totalLines":70}}}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01M1Yq2UQKJQaWrTpiBtQjFw","type":"tool_result","content":"# ray/dashboard_exposure\n# Expose Ray dashboard on port 8265 via the ray-head Service\n\nprompt: |\n  The Ray dashboard should be reachable from inside the cluster, but the\n  ray-head Service only exposes the GCS port.\n\n  Your task: update the ray-head Service to expose the dashboard on port {{params.dashboard_port}}.\n\n  Use this command to test:\n  ```bash\n  kubectl -n ray exec curl-test -- curl -sS -o /dev/null -w \"%{http_code}\" \\\n    http://ray-head:{{params.dashboard_port}}/api/cluster_status\n  ```\n\n  Success criteria: the command returns HTTP 200.\n\nparams:\n  dashboard_port:\n    default: 8265\n    description: Port on the ray-head Service that exposes the Ray dashboard\n\nnamespace_contract:\n  required_roles: []\n\nmetrics:\n  - time_to_first_mutation\n\npreconditionUnits:\n  - name: ray_env_ready\n    on_probe_fail: skip\n    probe:\n      - command: \"kubectl -n ray get pods 2>/dev/null | grep -c Running\"\n        timeout_sec: 10\n    apply:\n      - command: \"/bin/sh -c 'kubectl delete namespace ray --ignore-not-found=true --wait=false; kubectl wait --for=delete namespace/ray --timeout=300s 2>/dev/null || true'\"\n        timeout_sec: 360\n        sleep: 2\n      - command: \"kubectl create namespace ray\"\n        sleep: 0\n      - command: \"kubectl -n ray apply -f cases/ray/dashboard_exposure/resource/ray-head-service.yaml\"\n        sleep: 1\n      - command: \"kubectl -n ray apply -f cases/ray/dashboard_exposure/resource/ray-head.yaml\"\n        sleep: 2\n      - command: \"kubectl -n ray rollout status deploy/ray-head --timeout=600s\"\n        sleep: 2\n      - command: \"kubectl -n ray apply -f cases/ray/dashboard_exposure/resource/ray-worker.yaml\"\n        sleep: 2\n      - command: \"kubectl -n ray rollout status deploy/ray-worker --timeout=600s\"\n        sleep: 2\n      - command: \"/bin/sh -c 'kubectl -n ray get pod curl-test >/dev/null 2>&1 || kubectl -n ray apply -f cases/ray/dashboard_exposure/resource/curl-test.yaml'\"\n        sleep: 1\n      - command: \"kubectl -n ray wait --for=condition=Ready pod/curl-test --timeout=600s\"\n        timeout_sec: 660\n        sleep: 1\n    verify:\n      - command: \"kubectl -n ray get pods 2>/dev/null | grep -c Running\"\n        timeout_sec: 10\n\n  # Additive fixture unit (Rule 4): the oracle's HTTP check execs into the\n  # curl-test pod. Standalone, ray_env_ready's apply creates it. But in a\n  # workflow where this case inherits a live cluster from a prior stage (deploy\n  # /scale), ray_env_ready's apply is skipped and no prior case creates\n  # curl-test, so the oracle would fail with no test pod. This unit ensures JUST\n  # the curl-test pod idempotently, gated by its own probe, WITHOUT touching the\n  # cluster/namespace. Standalone it is a harmless no-op (the pod already exists).\n  - name: curl_test_ready\n    on_probe_fail: skip\n    probe:\n      - command: \"kubectl -n ray get pod curl-test 2>/dev/null | grep -c curl-test\"\n        timeout_sec: 10\n    apply:\n      - command: \"/bin/sh -c 'kubectl -n ray get pod curl-test >/dev/null 2>&1 || kubectl -n ray apply -f cases/ray/dashboard_exposure/resource/curl-test.yaml'\"\n        sleep: 1\n      - command: \"kubectl -n ray wait --for=condition=Ready pod/curl-test --timeout=600s\"\n        timeout_sec: 660\n        sleep: 1\n    verify:\n      - command: \"kubectl -n ray get pod curl-test 2>/dev/null | grep -c curl-test\"\n        timeout_sec: 10\n\noracle:\n  verify:\n    commands:\n      - command: \"python3 cases/ray/dashboard_exposure/oracle/oracle.py\"\n        timeout_sec: 180\n===\n# ray/upgrade_version\n# Upgrade ray-head and ray-worker deployments from rayproject/ray:2.8.0 to 2.9.0\n\nprompt: |\n  A Ray cluster is running with an older Ray image ({{params.from_image}}).\n\n  Your task: upgrade both ray-head and ray-worker deployments to\n  {{params.to_image}}.\n\n  Requirements:\n  - Update the image in both deployments.\n  - Ensure rollouts complete successfully.\n\n  Suggested commands:\n  ```bash\n  kubectl -n ray set image deploy/ray-head ray-head={{params.to_image}}\n  kubectl -n ray set image deploy/ray-worker ray-worker={{params.to_image}}\n  kubectl -n ray rollout status deploy/ray-head --timeout=120s\n  kubectl -n ray rollout status deploy/ray-worker --timeout=120s\n  ```\n\n  Success criteria: both deployments use {{params.to_image}} and remain ready.\n\nparams:\n  from_image:\n    default: rayproject/ray:2.8.0\n    description: Current Ray image the cluster is running before the upgrade\n  to_image:\n    default: rayproject/ray:2.9.0\n    description: Target Ray image to upgrade both deployments to\n\nnamespace_contract:\n  required_roles: []\n\nmetrics:\n  - time_to_first_mutation\n\npreconditionUnits:\n  - name: ray_env_ready\n    on_probe_fail: skip\n    probe:\n      - command: \"kubectl -n ray get pods 2>/dev/null | grep -c Running\"\n        timeout_sec: 10\n    apply:\n      - command: \"/bin/sh -c 'kubectl delete namespace ray --ignore-not-found=true --wait=false; kubectl wait --for=delete namespace/ray --timeout=300s 2>/dev/null || true'\"\n        timeout_sec: 360\n        sleep: 2\n      - command: \"kubectl create namespace ray\"\n        sleep: 0\n      - command: \"kubectl -n ray apply -f cases/ray/upgrade_version/resource/ray-head-service.yaml\"\n        sleep: 1\n      - command: \"kubectl -n ray apply -f cases/ray/upgrade_version/resource/ray-head.yaml\"\n        sleep: 2\n      - command: \"kubectl -n ray rollout status deploy/ray-head --timeout=600s\"\n        sleep: 2\n      - command: \"kubectl -n ray apply -f cases/ray/upgrade_version/resource/ray-worker.yaml\"\n        sleep: 2\n      - command: \"kubectl -n ray rollout status deploy/ray-worker --timeout=600s\"\n        sleep: 2\n      - command: \"/bin/sh -c 'kubectl -n ray get pod ray-client >/dev/null 2>&1 || kubectl -n ray apply -f cases/ray/upgrade_version/resource/ray-client.yaml'\"\n        sleep: 1\n      - command: \"kubectl -n ray wait --for=condition=Ready pod/ray-client --timeout=600s\"\n        timeout_sec: 660\n        sleep: 1\n    verify:\n      - command: \"kubectl -n ray get pods 2>/dev/null | grep -c Running\"\n        timeout_sec: 10\n\noracle:\n  verify:\n    commands:\n      - command: \"python3 cases/ray/upgrade_version/oracle/oracle.py\"\n        timeout_sec: 180\n===\noracle\nresource\ntest.yaml\noracle\nresource\ntest.yaml","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c1e8bedf-f5ad-4053-89b1-0392388ebd2b","uuid":"72abe545-d01b-4c8b-8556-b2117a4b6465","timestamp":"2026-06-26T05:15:41.750Z","tool_use_result":{"stdout":"# ray/dashboard_exposure\n# Expose Ray dashboard on port 8265 via the ray-head Service\n\nprompt: |\n  The Ray dashboard should be reachable from inside the cluster, but the\n  ray-head Service only exposes the GCS port.\n\n  Your task: update the ray-head Service to expose the dashboard on port {{params.dashboard_port}}.\n\n  Use this command to test:\n  ```bash\n  kubectl -n ray exec curl-test -- curl -sS -o /dev/null -w \"%{http_code}\" \\\n    http://ray-head:{{params.dashboard_port}}/api/cluster_status\n  ```\n\n  Success criteria: the command returns HTTP 200.\n\nparams:\n  dashboard_port:\n    default: 8265\n    description: Port on the ray-head Service that exposes the Ray dashboard\n\nnamespace_contract:\n  required_roles: []\n\nmetrics:\n  - time_to_first_mutation\n\npreconditionUnits:\n  - name: ray_env_ready\n    on_probe_fail: skip\n    probe:\n      - command: \"kubectl -n ray get pods 2>/dev/null | grep -c Running\"\n        timeout_sec: 10\n    apply:\n      - command: \"/bin/sh -c 'kubectl delete namespace ray --ignore-not-found=true --wait=false; kubectl wait --for=delete namespace/ray --timeout=300s 2>/dev/null || true'\"\n        timeout_sec: 360\n        sleep: 2\n      - command: \"kubectl create namespace ra